The course will cover the legal and international challenges democratic instruments face domestically and internationally, discuss case studies from Estonia and abroad, and analyse scholarly research on these topics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course will give an insight into the organization and administration of elections and other democratic instruments such as petitions. The objective will be to understand the complexities of organizing these key events in a democracy, including their observation. The course is focusing also on its electronic derivates, such as the organization of electronic voting, participation, and participatory budgeting, amongst others.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students completing the course will (1) understand and have an overview of the key components and complexities that are involved in organizing elections, (2) be able to analyze the use of a democratic instrument in a given context using international standards, (3) be able to derive (technical) requirements for the implementation of democratic instruments using electronic means, and (4) have a reflective understanding of their own role in such processes whether as participant, candidate, organizer or observer.
